This lab demonstrated practical techniques for analyzing session management security. You learned to:

Capture and decode session cookies using Burp Suite
Measure token entropy to assess randomness
Identify common vulnerabilities like missing security flags and predictable patterns
Automate security testing with Python scripts
Key Takeaways:

Strong session tokens require high entropy (> 128 bits recommended)
Security attributes (HttpOnly, Secure, SameSite) are critical for cookie protection
Predictable patterns in tokens enable session hijacking attacks
Automated scanning helps identify vulnerabilities at scale
